# Development happens on Windows, deployment on Linux. Storing every
# text file with LF keeps the repository identical for both, and stops
# a CRLF checkout from leaking into a commit — which matters for the
# shell scripts and the systemd unit, where CRLF is a syntax error.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binaries and certificates must never be touched.
*.pem   binary
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.gz    binary
